{"type": "article", "id": 4808, "title": "Seams 系列花瓶", "description": "", "date": "2014-12-30T08:10:48Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [], "category": 25, "column": 28, "author": 1329, "comment_count": 3, "praise_count": 8, "image": "img/article/article_show/20160605233656To8SKCtJrl2YenhA.jpg", "contents": "\n\n<p>\r\n\t英国设计师 Benjamin Hubert 今年推出了一系列名为「Seams」的花瓶，seams 直译过来就是接缝处的意思，在 Benjamin Hubert 看来，在制作产品时，不管是塑胶还是陶瓷，只要使用到模具，就避免不了接缝的出现，之后还得靠人工将那些接缝处修补平整。这一次 Benjamin Hubert 决定反其道而行之，故意将模具拆分，让容器在灌浆的过程中留下深深的接缝线。于是，接缝线成为了这一系列新品的特色，他特意选用了雾面无光泽的釉料来衬托接缝处，反倒是透出特别的美感。定价 230－275 英镑（约合人民币 2230－2666 元）不等，<a href=\"http://www.benjaminhubert.co.uk/works/object/seams/\" target=\"_blank\">点击这里尝试购买</a>。\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160605233652UTcyxeK7pVloANqS.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\"><img src=\"img/uploads/20160605233653pyMt8Cd6UI1T7NAb.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\"><img src=\"img/uploads/20160605233653msP58cRCrJoK6UTZ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\"><img src=\"img/uploads/201606052336541iv2Vgf5H6F9j3At.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\"><img src=\"img/uploads/20160605233654EKXsZoGtMHSJvkmF.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</p>\n\n\n"}